class property loggerÔÉÅ

Instances of the Logger class represent a single logging channel. A ‚Äúlogging channel‚Äù indicates an area of an application. Exactly how an ‚Äúarea‚Äù is defined is up to the application developer. Since an application can have any number of areas, logging channels are identified by a unique string. Application areas can be nested (e.g. an area of ‚Äúinput processing‚Äù might include sub-areas ‚Äúread CSV files‚Äù, ‚Äúread XLS files‚Äù and ‚Äúread Gnumeric files‚Äù). To cater for this natural nesting, channel names are organized into a namespace hierarchy where levels are separated by periods, much like the Java or Python package namespace. So in the instance given above, channel names might be ‚Äúinput‚Äù for the upper level, and ‚Äúinput.csv‚Äù, ‚Äúinput.xls‚Äù and ‚Äúinput.gnu‚Äù for the sub-levels. There is no arbitrary limit to the depth of nesting.
